586
00:27:04,053 --> 00:27:06,554
The problem is, in a lot of first-person games, a lot of

587
00:27:06,574 --> 00:27:07,534
people don't tend to look up.

588
00:27:07,574 --> 00:27:10,475
So players would come to this, and then they'd turn around

589
00:27:10,495 --> 00:27:11,296
thinking it was a dead end.

590
00:27:11,316 --> 00:27:13,216
So that was one problem.

591
00:27:13,677 --> 00:27:16,058
And another problem was, if you started going backwards,

592
00:27:16,098 --> 00:27:17,438
the hallway looked exactly the same.

593
00:27:18,330 --> 00:27:20,051
And that happens a lot because of the gravity changing

594
00:27:20,091 --> 00:27:20,471
mechanic.

595
00:27:20,511 --> 00:27:21,651
It's very easy to get turned around.

596
00:27:22,132 --> 00:27:23,232
So a lot of people would backtrack

597
00:27:23,252 --> 00:27:24,492
through an entire hallway until they

